# Section D – Verification & Review Plan

## D.1 Model Validation Metrics

| Metric | Threshold | Tier Applicability | Measurement Method |
|---|---|---|---|
| AUC-ROC | ≥ 0.80 (synthetic), ≥ 0.75 (real) | Per domain | Scikit-learn `roc_auc_score` on held-out test set |
| Sensitivity (Recall) | ≥ 0.85 for High/Critical | High, Critical | Confusion matrix; class-weighted |
| Specificity | ≥ 0.75 | Low, Medium | Confusion matrix |
| Expected Calibration Error (ECE) | ≤ 0.05 | All | `calibration_curve` + ECE calculation |
| Brier Score | ≤ 0.15 | All | `brier_score_loss` |
| F1-Score (macro) | ≥ 0.75 | All | `f1_score(average='macro')` |
| Fairness: AUC gap by gender | ≤ 0.05 | All | Disaggregated AUC; Fairness Indicators library |
| Fairness: FNR gap by geography | ≤ 0.05 | High, Critical | FNR per state/district stratum |

All metrics computed on a stratified held-out test set (20% of training data, stratified by age band, gender, and geographic tier).

---

## D.2 False-Negative Monitoring Strategy

**Rationale:** A false negative at High or Critical tier means a child at developmental risk is not flagged, potentially missing intervention. This is the highest-consequence error class.

### Operational Monitoring Protocol

1. **Static Threshold Override:** For High and Critical tiers, calibrated probability thresholds are set asymmetrically: sensitivity-first (favour recall over precision). The threshold is a configurable parameter, not hard-coded.
2. **Sentinel Case Review:** A random 5% sample of Low/Medium-flagged children are selected monthly for supervised re-review by Supervisors. Discrepancies between system tier and Supervisor re-assessment are logged as potential false negatives.
3. **Drift-Triggered FNR Audit:** If Population Stability Index (PSI) of input features exceeds 0.2 (model distribution drift), a mandatory FNR re-audit is triggered.
4. **Referral Outcome Tracking:** If referral outcome data becomes available (e.g., clinical assessment post-referral), it is used as a retrospective ground truth to compute real-world FNR.
5. **Alert Rule:** If computed FNR for Critical tier exceeds 12% over a rolling 90-day window, a P1 alert is raised to the ML team and government programme officer.

