## D.3 Integration Test Plan

### API Integration Tests

All tests run in CI/CD pipeline on every pull request against a staging environment with seeded test data.

| Test ID | Test Description | Method | Pass Criteria |
|---|---|---|---|
| INT-001 | Child registration → assessment → risk result end-to-end | Pytest (HTTP client) | 200 OK at each step; risk result returned with tier + SHAP values |
| INT-002 | AWW role cannot access Supervisor endpoints | Pytest (role-boundary) | 403 Forbidden returned |
| INT-003 | Supervisor cannot access data outside own block | Pytest (data-scoping) | Child records from other blocks return 404/403 |
| INT-004 | Consent revocation triggers data access hold | Pytest | Subsequent read returns 403 until resolved |
| INT-005 | Sync push with new records creates server records correctly | Pytest | Server DB record count matches push payload |
| INT-006 | Sync push with conflicting records triggers resolution | Pytest | Server returns reconciled record; audit log records conflict event |
| INT-007 | Audit log entry created for every write operation | Pytest | audit_log table has correct entry after each create/update |
| INT-008 | Batch risk recalculation updates all records in cohort | Pytest (async job) | All records in test cohort have updated risk_results after job completion |
| INT-009 | Analytics endpoint returns correct aggregates for district | Pytest | Expected count, tier distributions match test data |
| INT-010 | Token expiry forces re-authentication | Pytest | Expired token returns 401; valid refresh token returns new access token |

---

## D.4 Offline Sync Failure Testing

Tests run on physical Android devices and emulators with network conditions artificially throttled using Android Emulator network control or `tc` (traffic control) on test server.

| Test ID | Scenario | Method | Pass Criteria |
|---|---|---|---|
| SYNC-001 | 72-hour offline, 200 records queued, then reconnect | Physical device test | All 200 records sync successfully; no duplicates; audit log reflects sync event |
| SYNC-002 | Partial sync interrupted mid-flight (connection drop) | Emulator + network drop | WorkManager retries; no data corruption; sync completes on reconnect |
| SYNC-003 | Same record edited offline on two devices concurrently | Two-emulator test | Server conflict manager produces single canonical record; both devices reflect resolved state |
| SYNC-004 | Sync push with malformed payload (tampered data) | Pytest (malformed request) | API returns 400; no partial records written; audit log records rejected payload |
| SYNC-005 | Sync under 2G-equivalent bandwidth (50kbps, 500ms latency) | Emulator + throttled network | Sync completes within 5 minutes for 200 records; no timeout errors |
| SYNC-006 | Device clock skew of ±30 minutes | Emulator with clock offset | Conflict resolution uses server timestamp authoritatively; no ordering errors |
| SYNC-007 | App killed mid-sync | Physical device test | WorkManager resumes sync on next launch; no records lost or duplicated |

---

## D.5 Security Testing Checklist

### Web Application (OWASP Top 10 Alignment)

| Check | Tool | Pass Criteria |
|---|---|---|
| SQL Injection | OWASP ZAP, manual | No injection vulnerability in any parameterised query |
| Broken Authentication | Burp Suite | JWT not accepted without valid signature; refresh tokens cannot be reused |
| Sensitive Data Exposure | Manual review, ssl-labs equivalent | TLS 1.3 enforced; no PII in API error messages; no PII in logs |
| RBAC Boundary | Manual + automated tests | No privilege escalation across roles possible |
| Security Misconfiguration | Trivy (container), testssl.sh | No critical container vulnerabilities; TLS A-grade |
| XSS | OWASP ZAP | No stored or reflected XSS in dashboard inputs |
| CSRF | Manual | SameSite cookie attribute set; CSRF tokens on state-changing requests |
| Rate Limiting | Load test (k6) | API rate limiting enforced (e.g., 100 req/min per token) |
| Audit Trail Integrity | Manual review | Audit log chaining verifiable; no rows deletable without detection |

### Android Application

| Check | Tool | Pass Criteria |
|---|---|---|
| Local data encryption | Manual + SQLCipher verification | All DB files encrypted; unreadable without key |
| Network traffic inspection | mitmproxy | Certificate pinning enforced; no cleartext traffic |
| Reverse engineering risk | APKTool + ProGuard verify | ProGuard obfuscation applied; no API keys in APK |
| Exported components | Manual AndroidManifest review | No unintentionally exported activities/receivers |
| Root detection bypass | Manual on rooted device | App detects root and warns user (or restricts sync) |

---

## D.6 Governance Compliance Audit Checklist

This checklist is used for the annual governance compliance audit, conducted by the government DPO or appointed auditor.

### DPDP Act 2023 Compliance

| Requirement | Control | Evidence Location | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| Valid consent before data collection | Consent capture in app; consent table | `consents` table; AWW app consent screen | To verify |
| Consent is informed and in local language | Consent text shown in regional language | AWW app UI + consent_text field | To verify |
| Purpose limitation – data used only for stated purpose | API data access restricted by role; no third-party data sharing | RBAC config; DPA | To verify |
| Data minimisation | Only required fields collected per indicator framework | Data Minimisation Audit (D1.4) | To verify |
| Data accuracy | AWW field validation; Supervisor review | App validation rules; supervisor review workflow | To verify |
| Consent revocation mechanism | Revoke endpoint; data access hold on revocation | `/api/v1/consent/{id}` DELETE; audit log | To verify |
| Data principal rights (access, correction) | Not yet applicable (children as data principals; guardian rights mechanism) | Legal review required | Open |
| Data retention limits | 5-year retention policy; scheduled purge of non-essential fields | Retention policy document; scheduled DB purge job | To verify |
| Data breach notification ≤72 hours | Breach Response Plan; Grafana anomaly alerts | `data_breach_response_plan.md` | To verify |
| Government data ownership | DPA; no vendor data lock-in | Data Ownership Agreement; MinIO on-prem | To verify |

### System Governance

| Audit Area | Audit Activity | Frequency |
|---|---|---|
| Model Governance | Review model version, last retraining date, drift metrics | Quarterly |
| Access Control | Review Keycloak user list; deactivate leavers | Monthly |
| Audit Log Integrity | Verify checksum chain for previous month's log | Monthly |
| Penetration Testing | Full pen test by external assessor | Annual |
| Consent Registry | Sample audit of consent records vs. active child records | Quarterly |
| Data Minimisation | Review any new fields added since last audit | Semi-annual |
| Disaster Recovery | DR drill and documented RTO/RPO results | Annual |
| Model Bias Review | Run Bias Report on latest real-world data | Annual (or at retraining) |

